# Portfolio (juliet-gobran.com.au)

## Active build

- **Target:** Next.js App Router — Home (`/`), project detail (`/projects/[slug]`), About (`/about`)
- **Design reference:** Figma frame `359:1096` in file `2qIoGOLmiSESnYiqVLyHco`
- **Do not build** legacy `/home-v2` route unless explicitly asked

## Before editing code

1. Read relevant docs in `docs/portfolio/`:
   - `site-map.md` — pages and routes
   - `nextjs.md` — project structure and commands
   - `content-schema.md` — project JSON format
   - `figma.md` — frame structure and mapping
   - `design-tokens.md` — colors, fonts, spacing (Figma source)
   - `styles.md` — **use these CSS/Tailwind mappings first**
2. **Prefer design tokens** — use CSS variables from `src/styles/tokens.css` and Tailwind theme extensions; avoid hardcoded values
3. Use **shared layout** for nav/footer (app shell), not duplicated per page
4. Use **client components** only when needed (e.g. live Wollongong clock)
5. Do not deploy to production without explicit user approval

## Voice and content

- Title: **Senior Product Designer**
- Tone: friendly, professional, not corporate
- Nav links: LinkedIn (`https://www.linkedin.com/in/juliet-gobran/`), Medium (`https://medium.com/@juliet.gobran`)

## Workflow

```text
Figma (design) → docs/portfolio/ (specs) → Next.js (implementation)
```

When implementing from Figma, match tokens in `design-tokens.md`. When updating project copy, edit JSON in `content/projects/`. Prefer docs over guessing.

## Content

- One JSON file per project in `content/projects/`
- Images in `public/images/projects/{slug}/`
- Only `published` projects appear on the home page (drafts are excluded)
